      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When 2-methyl-2,5-pentanediol is treated with sulfuric acid, dehydration occurs and 2,2-dimethyltetrahydrofuran is formed. Suggest a mechanism for this reaction. Which of the two oxygen atoms is most likely to be eliminated, and why?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbzhYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3f59b2f898fd9ca6e5d11bf31629fdf1ce2ef4d8/OChem_18_EC_029.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 2,2-dimethyltetrahydrofuran. It comprises a five-membered ring incorporating one oxygen, connected to two methyl groups at C2.\">",
